# Build artifacts from the Nim perception library.
#
# The library rebuilds on-demand via ``build.py::ensure_library`` on
# first policy import (source-hash gated), so there's no benefit to
# committing the compiled output — and it's platform-specific, so
# committing it would just cause spurious diffs between macOS /
# Linux runners. Matches the repo-wide rule in ``MISSION.md``
# ("Never commit built .so / .dylib / .dll").
libmodulabot_perception.so
libmodulabot_perception.dylib
libmodulabot_perception.dll
*.sources
nimcache/
__pycache__/
